    <note type="biography">
        <p>Soldier and agriculturalist. Son of John Le Couteur (1760–1835). Commander of the Jersey Militia. Founder and president, Royal Jersey Agricultural Society. Author of a well-known work on wheat (1836). Displayed 104 varieties of wheat at the Great Exhibition of 1851. FRS 1843.</p></note>
